d. NFE may on behalf and with the advice of its Members establish and administer phytosanitary protocols for the purpose
of qualifying the Products for Export Markets. 
e. NFE may on behalf and with the advice of its Members provide market entry and development assistance, including
related administrative and promotional services, to its Members. 
f. NFE may on behalf and with the advice of its Members negotiate and enter into agreements with providers of transportation
services for export of the Products. 
g. NFE may recover administrative expenses and costs related to qualifying and preparing Members' Products for export
through fees and assessments allocated to each Member on a pro-rata share basis or any other non discriminatory method.
