storage, and treatment meet the requirements established by a relevant foreign government so that the Members' goods
will qualify for importation into the country subject to such requirements. 
j. NFE may on behalf and with the advice of its Members allocate the capacity of facilities, time of domestic and foreign
inspection personnel, and other resources of NFE amongst the Members engaged in the shipment of Products for export,
provided that such allocations are based on shipment quantities or other non-discriminatory criteria. 



